Docker Port Mapping:

Port mapping lets you connect a port on your host system â†’ to a port inside the container.

docker run -p <HOST_PORT>:<CONTAINER_PORT> <image_name>

docker run -d -p 8087:80 --name blog  nginx:alpine-perl


=========================================DONE===============================================

DOCKER COMPOSE FILE FOR HTTPD:

version: '3'

services:
  webapp:
    image: httpd:latest
    container_name: httpd
    ports:
      - "3001:80"   #host port:container_port
    volumes:
      - /opt/itadmin:/usr/local/apache2/htdocs  #Volume Mapping == Host volume: Container_volume


---------------------------
CMD : docker compose up -d  # -d = detach mode

===========================================END================================================
